## Implementation Notes for Current Prototype Revision
1. Use Socket.IO as the primary live data channel.
2. Load history once on connect, then stream incremental metric updates from the socket.
3. Do not poll `/api/snapshot` every second from the client unless a deliberate fallback is reintroduced later.
4. Avoid full-card flash animations on every update; keep metric refresh visually stable.
5. Show human-readable local browser time in the top-right clock and localised times in the event log labels.
6. Start the background publisher with Flask-SocketIO background task helpers instead of a raw Python thread so the dev server remains stable.
7. Keep the prototype clean and reliable; fancy interactions are optional, clarity is required.
